newsitem.title: UK: NWE jet fuel quiet, focus on Med arb to east.
newsitem.headline: NWE jet fuel quiet, focus on Med arb to east.

text.p: European jet fuel traders focused on a potential arb from the Med to Asia on Wednesday, with premiums for both EU and non-EU qualified material talked firmer, traders said.
Benchmark Dec IPE futures declined 50 cents to $216.50 a tonne after bouncing around in a narrow range in choppy, light trade.

Traders said strong Asian demand for jet fuel that has raised Singapore jet fuel prices may have opened an arb from the Med subject to shipping availabilities and timings. Values were talked $2 higher at fob Med high +$4/7, following the trade of an Algerian at fob high +$7.
NWE premiums were steady at Dec IPE +$32/33 with barges +$27/28.
